<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Dumbbell Bench Press</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/tailwindcss@3.2.0/dist/tailwind.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        /* Custom Styles */
        .hero-bg {
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ff0000, #000000);
            position: absolute;
            inset: 0;
            z-index: -10;
        }

        .card {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9); /* Semi-transparent background */
            border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
            border-radius: 1rem;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
            padding: 2rem;
            z-index: 10;
            position: relative;
        }

        .card:hover {
            transform: scale(1.02);
            box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        }

        .link {
            display: block;
            padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
            border-radius: 0.5rem;
            background: #ffffff;
            color: #ff0000;
            transition: background 0.3s ease, color 0.3s ease;
        }

        .link:hover {
            background: #ff0000;
            color: #ffffff;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body class="bg-gray-100 flex justify-center items-center min-h-screen p-4 relative">

    <div class="hero-bg"></div>

    <div class="card max-w-3xl w-full mx-auto mt-8 mb-8">
        <div>
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 text-center mb-8"><%= exerciseObj.name %></h1>

            <!-- Exercise Info -->
            <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
                <p class="text-xl text-gray-800"><strong>Sets:</strong> <%= exerciseObj.sets %> </p>
                <p class="text-xl text-gray-800"><strong>Reps:</strong> <%= exerciseObj.reps %> </p>
                <p class="text-xl text-gray-800"><strong>Focus:</strong> <%= exerciseObj.focus %> </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Exercise Detail -->
            <div class="mb-8">
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Exercise Details:</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
                    The dumbbell bench press is a fundamental chest exercise that helps build upper body strength. It targets the pectoral muscles, triceps, and shoulders. Using dumbbells allows for a greater range of motion compared to a barbell, activating stabilizer muscles.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Video List -->
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-6">YouTube Video Tutorials:</h2>
            <ul class="space-y-4">
                <li>
                    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iod1P3Efp4E" target="_blank" class="link hover:bg-red-600 hover:text-white">
                        Dumbbell Bench Press Tutorial - Form and Technique
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VmB1G1K7v94" target="_blank" class="link hover:bg-red-600 hover:text-white">
                        How to Perform Dumbbell Bench Press Safely
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OeSYmuHk7nE" target="_blank" class="link hover:bg-red-600 hover:text-white">
                        Common Mistakes in Dumbbell Bench Press and How to Fix Them
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6l65WFAnJvI" target="_blank" class="link hover:bg-red-600 hover:text-white">
                        Building Chest with Dumbbell Bench Press
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-CkHflbUE8Y" target="_blank" class="link hover:bg-red-600 hover:text-white">
                        Best Tips for Dumbbell Bench Press Progression
                    </a>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>

</html>
